Biceps?

44:17.422 --> 44:22.025
Whatever I want!

44:27.766 --> 44:28.898
Well, I doubt it.

44:28.900 --> 44:30.450
What do you mean?

44:30.451 --> 44:32.001
No one can carry
that much weight.

44:32.003 --> 44:34.103
You callin' me a liar?

44:34.105 --> 44:35.438
Wishful wishing.

44:37.425 --> 44:39.409
You'll wish you
didn't say that!

44:42.013 --> 44:43.746
Prove it to me then, Maximo.

44:44.916 --> 44:48.184
This pen that I use
for my note taking,

44:49.854 --> 44:51.454
how much do you think it weighs?

44:51.456 --> 44:52.456
An ounce?

44:53.792 --> 44:54.791
Less?

44:54.793 --> 44:58.895
I bet you can't even lift it.

44:58.897 --> 45:00.730
Give me that pen!

45:04.803 --> 45:08.771
Ow, what the heck?

45:16.881 --> 45:19.315
Even small me is
stronger than you.

45:22.954 --> 45:24.454
Watch.

45:28.359 --> 45:33.362
I'll lift this heavy table
with just one finger.

45:57.122 --> 46:00.823
My God, you are, you
are stronger than me.

46:02.527 --> 46:04.460
I've never felt good enough.

46:05.797 --> 46:08.131
I've never been strong enough.

46:08.133 --> 46:10.099
Everybody's always
been stronger.

46:11.136 --> 46:13.469
I'm, I'm nothing.

46:13.471 --> 46:14.471
I'm weak.

46:15.974 --> 46:17.473
I don't mean shit, do I, Doc?

46:22.213 --> 46:25.548
Does that mean I
gotta go now, Doc?

46:25.550 --> 46:27.550
Don't you wanna be strong?

46:30.355 --> 46:31.355
Yes.

46:33.258 --> 46:36.425
Maximo, I wanna
admit something to you.

46:37.996 --> 46:39.362
I hypnotized you.

46:40.231 --> 46:42.165
What?

46:42.166 --> 46:44.100
But now I shall bring you
out of your hypnotic state

46:44.102 --> 46:47.270
by the sound of the
snap of my fingers.

47:07.258 --> 47:08.258
You see?

47:10.028 --> 47:12.995
In order to test
your real strength,

47:12.997 --> 47:16.899
you need to use your
mind or your body.

47:16.901 --> 47:19.402
Your subconscious
mind is much stronger

47:19.404 --> 47:22.471
than any physical
part of your body.

47:24.209 --> 47:26.475
Watch, I'll show you.

47:39.490 --> 47:40.890
Hello?

47:47.031 --> 47:48.031
Oops.

48:03.948 --> 48:07.316
Now, read this.

48:08.953 --> 48:10.319
It's your own handwriting.

48:17.061 --> 48:18.527
I have a reoccurring dream.

48:20.598 --> 48:23.132
I have the strength
to kill myself.

48:28.406 --> 48:33.542
12 steps to end the addiction,
one step to beat it all.

48:36.347 --> 48:39.415
You say you can lift well
over your own weight, right?

48:41.519 --> 48:42.519
Yeah.

48:46.291 --> 48:48.691
Why don't we try that out?

48:53.031 --> 48:58.167
Now, you see this
is a special knot.

49:00.104 --> 49:03.239
Which will not get any
tighter than I want it

49:03.241 --> 49:06.108
so you don't have to be
afraid of strangling yourself.

49:08.146 --> 49:11.547
Now, pull this free
end as hard as you can.

49:11.549 --> 49:14.984
No matter the pain,
and hoist your

49:14.986 --> 49:16.986
entire body up up up and away.

49:22.994 --> 49:23.526
Up you go.

49:23.527 --> 49:24.527
Nice.
- Height.

49:25.196 --> 49:26.529
Keep pulling.

49:27.265 --> 49:28.265
Excellent.

49:29.200 --> 49:30.433
Keep pulling.

49:32.003 --> 49:33.003
Heights.

49:33.604 --> 49:35.404
They make me nauseous.

49:35.405 --> 49:37.205
Overcome your fears, Maximo.

49:37.208 --> 49:38.407
Keep pulling.

49:44.415 --> 49:47.483
Just another inch, and
you're off the ground.

49:54.559 --> 49:57.293
Yes, yes you are Samson.

49:57.295 --> 49:59.595
Now pull yourself up, pull!

50:00.631 --> 50:01.631
Higher!

50:07.739 --> 50:09.038
There you go!

50:09.040 --> 50:10.639
Do you feel strong now?

50:10.641 --> 50:11.641
Woo-wee.

50:12.777 --> 50:14.443
And you're there!

50:23.388 --> 50:25.354
Keep going, Samson.

50:25.356 --> 50:29.191
Aye aye aye aye aye
aye, up up up and away!

50:30.595 --> 50:31.595
Woo-wee!

50:42.106 --> 50:43.739
That came right off.

51:49.707 --> 51:52.741
Would you pretend
to hang yourself?

52:36.320 --> 52:40.723
Sharon, I owe you your hour.

52:52.937 --> 52:53.937
Later.

53:51.462 --> 53:52.462
Sorry, later.

54:12.316 --> 54:13.482
Make any new friends?

54:13.484 --> 54:15.417
Yeah, the rats.

54:15.419 --> 54:17.586
When you said you'd start me
out with an entry level job

54:17.588 --> 54:19.688
I didn't know you
meant the basement.

54:19.690 --> 54:21.640
Yeah, well, when I started out

54:21.641 --> 54:23.721
I was cleaning up the dead
rats, so stop complaining.

54:25.630 --> 54:26.762
Got your pics.

54:31.636 --> 54:32.636
Nice trick.

54:33.604 --> 54:34.703
Gets trickier.

54:36.007 --> 54:37.606
Whoa, shit.

54:38.643 --> 54:39.643
How's that work?

54:41.045 --> 54:43.445
- If I told ya...
- You'd have to kill me?

54:44.315 --> 54:45.614
I'd have to kill them.

54:49.787 --> 54:51.654
So who are these guys you
had me trailing anyways?

54:51.656 --> 54:52.721
Police business.

54:54.859 --> 54:55.952
What the fuck, kid?

54:55.953 --> 54:57.046
- Hey.
- Are you some kind

54:57.047 --> 54:58.140
of goddamn voyeur or something?

54:58.141 --> 54:59.234
You said have fun.

54:59.235 --> 55:00.328
Yeah, I said have
fun with the targets,

55:00.331 --> 55:02.098
not me and my girl.

55:02.099 --> 55:03.866
Look, you shut me
out anyways, all right?

55:03.868 --> 55:05.334
Don't sweat it.

55:05.336 --> 55:06.336
Jesus.

55:07.905 --> 55:09.605
What's that thing?

55:09.607 --> 55:10.806
Still working on it.

55:10.808 --> 55:15.811
Look, I'm a snoop by
nature, but you get me out

55:15.813 --> 55:17.813
of this rat hole and into a car,

55:17.815 --> 55:19.548
I'll show you the
real stuff, all right?

55:19.550 --> 55:21.550
You're doing just fine
down here, kid, all right?

55:21.552 --> 55:23.669
There's rules and regulations.

55:23.670 --> 55:25.787
And rules and regulations
aren't gonna cut it anymore.

55:25.790 --> 55:28.357
I need a real job
with the department.

55:28.359 --> 55:30.092
Gotta be old enough,
smart enough, tough enough.

55:30.094 --> 55:31.827
Smart enough to know
you got something going on

55:31.829 --> 55:34.630
you don't want the
department knowing about.

55:34.632 --> 55:37.032
Smart enough but
not tough enough.

55:37.034 --> 55:38.767
Let me take a
bullet for you then.

55:38.769 --> 55:40.836
Prove it, I'm tougher
than you think.

55:40.838 --> 55:42.438
That's
what we all think.

55:44.642 --> 55:45.941
Do your own work then.

55:51.982 --> 55:54.083
You better watch
yourself, Gavin.

55:54.085 --> 55:56.418
Or I'll have you
parking the cars.

55:56.420 --> 55:59.922
If you, uh, ever get tired
of the dame you're with,

55:59.924 --> 56:02.858
and you're with a
nice getaway sticks,

56:02.860 --> 56:05.461
you'll make a great lover.

56:06.731 --> 56:08.164
What goes on
behind the curtain

56:08.165 --> 56:09.598
stays behind the
curtain with me.

56:11.001 --> 56:12.401
I'm dizzy for the dame.

56:12.403 --> 56:13.403
She's a keeper.

56:56.514 --> 56:58.147
Hold that, won't ya?

56:58.149 --> 56:59.848
Oh, thanks pal.

56:59.850 --> 57:01.317
Here, go like this.

57:01.318 --> 57:02.785
You look like you
could use a shower.

57:11.629 --> 57:13.595
Ladies and gentlemen,
boys and girls,

57:13.597 --> 57:18.066
children of all ages, welcome
to the greatest show on Earth.

57:18.068 --> 57:20.602
It's circus time!

57:22.606 --> 57:24.940
See the ferocious lions.

57:24.942 --> 57:27.543
Thrill to the
gargantuous elephants!

57:27.545 --> 57:29.878
Laugh to death with
America's favorite clown.

57:31.215 --> 57:34.149
And here he is,
Thumba the clown!

57:45.762 --> 57:48.029
Well, what do you think
of my act so far, Doc?

57:48.032 --> 57:50.899
How do you fit in the car?

57:50.901 --> 57:51.901
Can't tell ya.

58:00.544 --> 58:03.178
Love the smell
of breeze makeup.

58:03.180 --> 58:04.847
It's my mother's lipstick.

58:08.185 --> 58:09.785
Imagine.

58:09.787 --> 58:11.253
Thumba the circus clown,

58:11.255 --> 58:13.922
self-proclaimed
ambassador of humor.

58:14.792 --> 58:16.191
What's left of me, any way?

58:17.194 --> 58:18.660
Too pooped to pop.

58:21.832 --> 58:23.799
Clowns are supposed
to live forever.

58:25.970 --> 58:27.603
Laughs never ending.

58:31.141 --> 58:36.011
Came to radiation, chemo.

58:40.017 --> 58:41.617
I'm done with the laughs.

58:44.555 --> 58:46.755
You were in the
three ring today?

58:46.757 --> 58:49.892
Yeah, kids laughed, all right.

58:52.696 --> 58:56.698
Done my routine,
opened up my mouth,

58:57.568 --> 58:58.700
pantomime laughs.

59:00.104 --> 59:01.303
I did them for years.

59:01.305 --> 59:05.874
Rain or shine, always count
on the clown for laughs.

59:07.111 --> 59:12.247
Only, on this cloudy day I
was crying on the inside.

59:17.021 --> 59:20.656
What will make you
laugh again, Thumba?

59:23.861 --> 59:26.862
If the docs told me
they made a mistake.

59:29.867 --> 59:32.200
And that they
misdiagnosed it and

59:33.771 --> 59:35.804
it's just the chemo
that's killing me.

59:40.044 --> 59:41.743
Laughing my whole life.

59:44.815 --> 59:48.617
Guess it's my time
now to cry, cry, cry.

59:51.822 --> 59:52.822
Party's over.

01:00:04.635 --> 01:00:05.635
Thanks.

01:00:07.838 --> 01:00:09.204
I'm really sorry.

01:00:12.309 --> 01:00:13.842
Poison's taken my dignity.

01:00:21.051 --> 01:00:22.651
Oh, come on.

01:00:22.653 --> 01:00:24.119
Not you, too.

01:00:24.121 --> 01:00:25.121
Here.

01:00:31.328 --> 01:00:33.395
I guess it's me
acting the bozo now.

01:00:43.007 --> 01:00:44.940
Humor makes more out of chaos

01:00:44.942 --> 01:00:48.844
by dissolving
threatened anxiety.

01:00:52.082 --> 01:00:54.850
Psychoneuroimmunology
has been a breakthrough

01:00:54.852 --> 01:00:58.353
therapy for psychiatrists
in emotional healing.

01:01:03.127 --> 01:01:07.029
And the poor bum's head,
all I want is a chance

01:01:07.031 --> 01:01:09.765
to show that money
can't buy you happiness.

01:01:12.703 --> 01:01:13.703
That's good.

01:01:15.873 --> 01:01:18.707
Frankel, survivor
of the Holocaust.

01:01:19.977 --> 01:01:25.113
He says that, uh, humor is
another of the soul's weapons

01:01:26.884 --> 01:01:29.151
in the fight for
self-preservation.

01:01:31.889 --> 01:01:33.388
What's the matter?

01:01:33.390 --> 01:01:35.724
Business so bad you
can't afford a clock?

01:01:44.902 --> 01:01:45.902
Knock, knock.

01:01:47.004 --> 01:01:48.003
Who's there?

01:01:48.005 --> 01:01:49.404
Tank.

01:01:49.406 --> 01:01:50.472
Tank who?

01:01:50.474 --> 01:01:52.074
You're welcome.

01:01:56.180 --> 01:01:58.146
Oh, knock knock.

01:01:58.148 --> 01:01:59.081
Who is there?

01:01:59.083 --> 01:01:59.948
Wayne.

01:01:59.950 --> 01:02:02.117
Wayne who?

01:02:02.118 --> 01:02:04.285
Wayne, Wayne, go away,
come again another day.

01:02:05.956 --> 01:02:07.022
Knock, knock.

01:02:07.024 --> 01:02:08.023
Who's there?

01:02:08.025 --> 01:02:08.957
Acid.

01:02:08.959 --> 01:02:10.192
Acid who?

01:02:10.194 --> 01:02:12.894
Acid sit down and be quiet!

01:02:14.932 --> 01:02:15.797
Knock knock!

01:02:15.799 --> 01:02:16.465
Who's there?

01:02:16.467 --> 01:02:17.332
Disguise.

01:02:17.334 --> 01:02:19.101
Disguise who?

01:02:19.103 --> 01:02:21.369
This guy's killing me
with all these jokes!

01:02:27.311 --> 01:02:28.977
Knock knock!

01:02:28.979 --> 01:02:29.979
Who's there?

01:02:30.848 --> 01:02:32.314
Kill me.

01:02:32.316 --> 01:02:34.216
Kill me who?

01:02:34.218 --> 01:02:36.985
If the cancer don't kill
me, this balloon will.

01:02:39.857 --> 01:02:40.922
En garde!

01:02:45.129 --> 01:02:48.964
The doctor replied, don't
worry, I'll push you through.

01:02:51.135 --> 01:02:54.102
In the liver.

01:02:57.141 --> 01:02:58.940
I could die laughing with you.

01:03:01.011 --> 01:03:03.512
Any way.

01:03:03.513 --> 01:03:06.014
I feel a humor litany
snickering forth.

01:03:06.016 --> 01:03:07.015
Oxymoron.

01:03:07.017 --> 01:03:08.283
Jumbo shrimp.

01:03:09.119 --> 01:03:10.802
Dry wit.

01:03:10.803 --> 01:03:12.486
Why are hemorrhoids
called hemorrhoids

01:03:12.489 --> 01:03:14.956
instead of asteroids?

01:03:14.958 --> 01:03:17.959
Sarcasm, if you're having a
hard time laughing at yourself,

01:03:17.961 --> 01:03:19.427
I'd be happy to do it for ya.

01:03:21.098 --> 01:03:24.166
Oh, how many people
have telekinetic powers?

01:03:24.168 --> 01:03:25.867
Raise my hand.

01:03:27.437 --> 01:03:30.438
A laugh is the shortest
distance between two people.

01:03:32.543 --> 01:03:34.276
I'm sorry, Thumba.

01:03:35.045 --> 01:03:36.111
Laugh time's over.

01:03:43.420 --> 01:03:46.588
Wait.

01:03:50.027 --> 01:03:51.159
Can't stop now.

01:03:53.997 --> 01:03:54.997
I'm on a roll.

01:04:12.082 --> 01:04:13.615
Vaudeville slapstick!

01:04:13.617 --> 01:04:15.083
That's the best!

01:04:24.928 --> 01:04:27.495
Hey, Joe, whattaya know?

01:04:33.103 --> 01:04:36.104
That's what I call
a banana split!

01:04:40.110 --> 01:04:41.110
Whoa, oh.

01:04:43.046 --> 01:04:45.080
Shouldn't of done that.

01:05:28.392 --> 01:05:29.624
Oh man, come.

01:05:34.298 --> 01:05:36.631
Can't a clown have no dignity?

01:05:47.311 --> 01:05:49.311
It's clogged all the time.

01:05:49.313 --> 01:05:52.314
Couple of good plunges, all
your troubles down the drain.

01:05:53.684 --> 01:05:54.683
Thanks.

01:05:54.685 --> 01:05:56.318
Go for it.

01:06:00.390 --> 01:06:01.390
Freak.

01:06:05.128 --> 01:06:06.428
I hate bathroom humor.

01:06:21.411 --> 01:06:23.445
Pie in
the face slapstick.

01:06:25.215 --> 01:06:28.416
That's what I call
eating humble pie.

01:06:34.224 --> 01:06:35.490
You're killing me.

01:07:01.752 --> 01:07:03.518
Take the magic
seat, Detective.

01:07:03.520 --> 01:07:05.453
Tell me what's
been bothering you.

01:07:05.455 --> 01:07:07.188
Basically I'd like to
ask you some questions

01:07:07.190 --> 01:07:09.257
off the record if
that's okay, Doc.

01:07:10.494 --> 01:07:11.494
Sure.

01:07:13.730 --> 01:07:15.196
Chinese clock candle.

01:07:17.534 --> 01:07:19.534
You know clock history?

01:07:19.536 --> 01:07:20.802
Grandfather sure did.

01:07:20.804 --> 01:07:23.538
Owned a small clock
and watch repair.

01:07:28.745 --> 01:07:32.781
Had on display every known
time piece since time began.

01:07:35.218 --> 01:07:36.801
You charging for the hour, Doc?

01:07:36.802 --> 01:07:38.482
'Cause if so, I'll make
my questions quick.

01:07:43.660 --> 01:07:46.761
Oh no, on the house.

01:07:46.763 --> 01:07:49.664
Least I can do for
a public servant.

01:07:52.636 --> 01:07:54.369
Let's have a look.

01:07:56.506 --> 01:07:59.707
Oh, you're on antidepressants
for clinical depression,

01:07:59.709 --> 01:08:02.243
four years...
- That's now why I'm here, Doc

01:08:04.815 --> 01:08:06.581
The department shrink
prescribed those to me

01:08:06.583 --> 01:08:07.583
after my wi...

01:08:11.321 --> 01:08:16.457
After my wife was shot
and killed by a parolee.

01:08:20.529 --> 01:08:23.198
One who I arrested
for prior murder

01:08:23.200 --> 01:08:24.666
who should've got the chair.

01:08:35.679 --> 01:08:38.412
I hunted him down to an
abandoned warehouse, Doc.

01:08:40.216 --> 01:08:45.220
Just me, him, and
my Glock, alone.

01:08:46.423 --> 01:08:48.288
Wanted to put a
bullet in him bad.

01:08:50.627 --> 01:08:53.895
And I owe it to the
system that stopped me.

01:08:53.897 --> 01:08:57.198
After some bureaucratic
legal warfare with his lawyer

01:08:57.200 --> 01:09:00.234
concocting every
lie in the bad book.

01:09:00.237 --> 01:09:03.304
He walked away with a slap on
the wrist for breaking parole.

01:09:04.573 --> 01:09:07.774
And a misdemeanor for
peeing in the red zone.

01:09:11.180 --> 01:09:13.247
Rotten justice system,
Doc, I tell you.

01:09:15.385 --> 01:09:16.385
Pissed away.

01:09:19.923 --> 01:09:24.658
Anyways, the side effects
for the meds, they

01:09:24.661 --> 01:09:26.327
they made me suicidal.

01:09:27.596 --> 01:09:28.930
I nearly jumped a bridge.

01:09:32.669 --> 01:09:34.669
So he got away with murder.

01:09:37.941 --> 01:09:42.410
That musta been hard
for you to live with.

01:09:42.412 --> 01:09:43.877
Concession was that
me and the department

01:09:43.880 --> 01:09:45.947
came to a quiet understanding.

01:09:45.948 --> 01:09:47.948
Promotion to detective.

01:09:47.951 --> 01:09:49.417
No, I earned that.

01:09:49.419 --> 01:09:50.652
Oh, yes you did.

01:09:55.692 --> 01:09:58.359
How'd you wind up with
the folder anyways, Doc?

01:09:59.696 --> 01:10:01.463
Part of the settlement
was that it would

01:10:01.464 --> 01:10:03.231
never again see
the light of day.

01:10:03.233 --> 01:10:05.967
Was supposed to go into the
one-eyed purple paper eater.

01:10:07.771 --> 01:10:09.771
One-eyed purple paper eater.

01:10:20.517 --> 01:10:22.284
Burbed up evidence.

01:10:22.285 --> 01:10:24.052
Conscience nearly
shredded within.

01:10:24.053 --> 01:10:25.820
The one-eyed purple paper eater
regurgitated the settlement.

01:10:25.822 --> 01:10:29.390
Now drop that
detective staying pass.

01:10:29.392 --> 01:10:31.593
The only way to
make the truth last.

01:10:35.565 --> 01:10:37.999
I'm beginning to
take offense, Doc.

01:10:38.001 --> 01:10:40.001
Oh, Detective, please.

01:10:40.003 --> 01:10:42.470
My last patient was a clown.

01:10:43.406 --> 01:10:45.540
I'm just in a funny mood.

01:10:49.412 --> 01:10:50.812
Would you like some tea?

01:10:55.018 --> 01:10:57.318
Copy of the settlement.

01:11:04.327 --> 01:11:05.460
It's classified.

01:11:05.461 --> 01:11:06.741
Bureaucratic incompetence again.

01:11:10.567 --> 01:11:12.700
Typical misfiling.

01:11:12.702 --> 01:11:15.703
Was supposed to go
to psychiatry 0083,

01:11:15.705 --> 01:11:20.308
but winds up here,
psychiatry 8300.

01:11:22.512 --> 01:11:25.780
Too bad it wasn't your
settlement check they sent, huh?

01:11:44.367 --> 01:11:46.367
Things that
go bump in the night?

01:11:47.070 --> 01:11:48.070
Mice.

01:11:49.806 --> 01:11:51.406
Rats.

01:11:51.408 --> 01:11:52.640
Make a lot of thuds.

01:11:55.078 --> 01:11:58.613
What was it you wanted
to ask me, Detective?

01:12:08.491 --> 01:12:09.491
Patient?

